	   <tr><td colspan=2>Dropped in DS from the guys near the ME zone. No one else was in zone, so it rotted (no use to me and nodrop).<br><br>Luclin is broken, and Trivial Loot Code is why. They basically switched gears late in the the Luclin rollout to remove TLC, and the result is that many items that would make Luclin attractive are either nodrop (I've let so many things rot) or obscenely rare (which really hurts for quests).<br><br>I find this to be doubly true for the quest armor. I've now got at least one misc item or mark for every class but monk, and yet I've had only ONE jewel drop. They really need to bump up the drop rate on the jewels so that the armor quests can be completed without hunting long enough that you get to a level where the armor is useless to you!<br><br>Yes, if they bump up the drop rate, there will be farming. But as it is, farmers are just about the only ones who CAN complete the quests and derive any benefit (i.e. selling the resulting armor to lower level players).<br><br>Personally, I'm not bothering to hunt in Luclin with low-level characters. I'm farming with my high-levels and twinking the lower levels. I'd rather not. Luclin would be a fun place to hunt, but the drops are just too broken.<br><br>Oh well, I guess that's what I'm paying that extra $3/mo. for....<br><br>Places where I think they did it right: Twilight elementals; UP Elysians. Those are the right risk/effort/reward. Some of the uber-quests/encounters are also nicely done, and I get the sense that that's more where they spent their time... (<br><br>&nbsp;<br>You gain experience!<br>The Goblin Warlord hits YOU for 50 points!<br></td></tr>
