	   <tr><td colspan=2>So why is nodrop a bad thing?&nbsp;&nbsp;I mean there should be some items that aren't sold.  I am thinking that this is one of them.  I know I would have a problem with a low lvl ranger or cleric running around with a weapon like this that could easily destroy any mob it encountered.<br>As for it rotting away, if you are by yourself, that is how it goes.  If you aren't, offer it to the community that is there and see if somebody wants it.  If I wanted to get this item, I would join a group and try to hunt it.  Point is, it makes people work for it or at least have good luck to obtain it, not just plat.<br><br>As for hunting Luclin with low level characters, if you aren't, you are missing out.  Places like Paludal Caverns and Netherbian Lair are literally banks with open doors.  You get constant bronze drops, decent money drops, decent magic items, and rather easy quests.  Combine that with XP zones like Marus Seru, DSP, and Shadeweavers Thicket and you have a good formula for getting your characters up to high level quickly and easily.  On top of that you are going to end up with a nice bank account and that is always good.<br> <br>&nbsp;<br>Tuvin Kaga<br>Wood-Elf Ranger<br><br><br></td></tr>
